  "text": "Once the process requirements are given, the high temperature heat exchanger is designed using the same methods used for the typical heat exchangers. This subsection summarizes the basic logical structure of the process heat exchanger design procedure described by [CITATION_1] . Figure 6 shows the logical process for heat exchanger design. The fundamental goal of any such process is to find the optimal design among the infinite set of designs that could satisfy the thermal-hydraulic and mechanical requirements. Because of large number of qualitative factors in the design process, optimal needs are to be considered broadly. Generally, the design process aims at the least costly (which usually means the smallest) heat exchangers that meet the required thermal duty within the allowed pressure drops and satisfy the mechanical requirements. Fig. 6 . Basic logical structure of the process heat exchanger design procedure [CITATION_2] www.intechopen.com",
